transcripts: After 10 years testing prototypes to make the first cycling vacuum and another 20 building the only vacuum that won't lose suction I want them to last. So they're dropped 5 thousand times. Filled with 10 years of dust. Then hit 200 times. That's why Dyson vacuums last 10 years.
